help:source;help:so
                           so[urce] <path>

                  Read commands from the text file.
            White characters before commands are skipped.
          Everything from # to the end of line is skipped.
Spaces after command are skipped even when typed in the application.

     In braces, new-line characters are replaced by semicolons.

       In path:
         ~/... expands to the home folder
         %/... expands to the location of the application
